    %>
</div>
<div class=row>
  <div class="col-md-8 main-body pe-5">
    <div class="clearfix">
      <%=
        image_tag("https://res.cloudinary.com/saintpaulsnaples-org/image/upload/v1638208932/FrTomPentecost2021Scaled_qzwtu5.png",
        alt: "priest at altar" , width: "100%" ) %>

        <div class="mt-4">
          <%= cl_image_tag("pray_osljoq.jpg", width: "350" , class: "float-start me-3" ) %>

            <p><strong>Almighty God, who created us in your own image: Grant us
                grace fearlessly to contend against evil and to make no peace
                with oppression; and, that we may reverently use our freedom,
                help us to employ it in the maintenance of justice in our
                communities and among the nations, to the glory of your holy
                Name; through Jesus Christ our Lord, who lives and reigns with
                you and the Holy Spirit, one God, now and for ever. Amen.</strong>
            </p>
            <p class="text-end"> &mdash;Book of Common Prayer</p>
        </div>
        <h1>Join us in worship</h1>
        <%#= image_tag("https://saintpaulsnaplesorg.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/logos/Cross.jpg", width: "20%" ,
          class: "float-start pe-3" ) %>
          <%= cl_image_tag("cross-lent_rhj8ln.jpg", width: "140" , class: "float-start me-4" ) %>
            <p>Sundays at 8 a.m. and
              10 a.m. While masks are no longer required, please be considerate and help keep God's people safe
              (everyone is a child of God!)</p>
            <p>Our 10 a.m. service is live-streamed to <%= link_to "YouTube." ,
                ("https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCdc6lx-U_N1X26tkZ7TQ8-A") %>
            </p>
            <% if @bulletin.url.present? %>
              <p><strong>
                  <%= link_to "Here is the bulletin for #{@bulletin.date.strftime(" %A, %b %d")}", "#{@bulletin.url}" %>
                </strong></p>
              <% else %>
                <p>Sunday's bulletin will be available here on Thursday.</p>
                <% end %>

                  <p>To learn about our worship service and about the<strong> <em>Episcopal Church,</em></strong>
                    <%=link_to "click here" , worship_index_path %>. And click on that shelf of red books to get a
                      short,
                      cute introduction to our time-honored <em>Book of Common Prayer.</em>
                  </p>

                  <p>
                    <%= link_to "Click here for the on-line Book of Common Prayer" ,
                      ("https://www.churchpublishing.org/siteassets/pdf/book-of-common-prayer/book-of-common-prayer-2006.pdf")
                      %>
                  </p>


                  <p><strong>
                      <%= link_to "Click here for Scripture Readings" ,"http://www.lectionarypage.net" %>
                    </strong> </p>
    </div>
    <div class="clearfix">
      <h2 class-mt-3>Concert Feb. 22: 'Jodie DeSalvo in Concert'</h2>
      <%= cl_image_tag("jodiSm_fle4od.jpg", width: '60%' , class: "float-start img-fluid pe-2 clearfix" ) %>
        <div class="ms-2 mt-5">
          <!-- <div class="text-center">
            <h1 class="text-danger">Sold Out!</h1>
          </div> -->
          <p>Because of Covid, tickets are limited and masks, while not required, are encouraged. Thank you for helping
            to keep
            everyone safe. </p>
        </div>
        <div class="mt-4">
          <p><strong>
              <%= link_to "Click here to buy your tickets" , new_event_ticket_path(@event) %>
            </strong></p>
        </div>
    </div>
    <h2 class="mt-3">Reflect and Connect </h2>
    <p>This is a new small group that will meet at 10 a.m. Wednesdays in the library to ponder and discuss the lessons
      delivered the previous Sunday morning. No need to sign up, and sessions are stand-alone, meaning you can come any
      Wednesday without feeling "behind." All are welcome to sit in and participate
      fully or simply audit.</p>
    <h2 class="mt-3">Sacred Ground Series</h2>
    <p>This is a series of videos, readings and small-group discussions about race. This is highly
      recommended if you have questions about "critical race theory," a topic needlessly politicized. To
      watch an introduction, <%= link_to "click here. " , "https://www.episcopalchurch.org/sacred-ground/" %>



        <%= cl_image_tag("FarmMarketLogoOutreach2_up8pqz.png", class: "mx-auto d-block my-5" , width: "50%" ) %>

          <h2 class="mt-3">Home of the great Farmers' Market</h2>

          <p>Welcome to the easy in-and-out St. Paul's Farmer's Market! Stop by the hospitality pit and
            introduce yourself to new friends and have a hot dog, on us! The market is now open, through
            next April, Saturdays from 8 a.m.to noon. Browse and buy books, jewelery and lots of produce.
          </p>
          <p>For more information about the market, <%= link_to "click here." , markets_index_path %>
          </p>
          <div class="clearfix"></div>
          <h2 class="mt-3">Meet our new bishop</h2>
          <%= image_tag("https://image.isu.pub/220312142840-605a6914d9d727628bb7dc3ee48014d7/jpg/page_1.jpg",
            alt: "diocese booklet" , class: "float-start img-fluid pe-2" , width: "40%" ) %>
            <p>
              <%= link_to "Click here" ,
                ("https://issuu.com/episcopalflorida/docs/2022_special_convention_book_final_to_print_-_sing") %> to
                learn about four priests, one of whom will be our next bishop.
            </p>
            <p>A special convention will be held April 2 for the election of a bishop coadjutor, and three delegates
              from St. Paul's will be voting. Once ordained later in the year, the new bishop will be under the tutelage
              of Bishop Dabney Smith until the fifth bishop of our diocese retires and the sixth takes his place.
            </p>
            <div class="clearfix"></div>
            <!-- <h2 class="mt-3">Supporters of these children</h2>
          <%=cl_image_tag("25_aeyuf2.jpg", width: "420" , height: "315" , class:"float-start pe-3") %>
            <p>Episcopalians of the Naples Deanery have been supporting the children at a shelter in the
              Dominican Republic for the last 18 years. The <em>Albergue el Buen Samaritano</em> in San
              Francisco de Macoris, serves a hundred children who would be on the street were it not for the
              shelter. The kids arrive for breakfast, learn their abcs and social skills and get lots of
              love that may otherwise be missing in their young lives. It is a ministry of love and
              affection, above all.</p>
            <div class="clearfix"></div> -->

            <h2 class="mt-3">Supporters of Tumaini Fund</h2>
            <%= cl_image_tag("SusanWilson_dvvx0e.jpg", width: "60%" , class: "float-end ms-3" ) %>
              <p>Dr. Susan Wilson, an English family physician, is full of energy and zealfor the Lord. She
                founded <em>Tumaini </em>(the word means "hope") <em> Fund </em> to put her faith to work in
                the AIDS-ravaged Kagera region of Northwest Tanzania. There she established an orphanage for
                thousands of children who lost their moms and dads to AIDS. In addition to monitary
                contributions, the ladies of our church, the ECW (Episcopal Church Women) have sewn numerous
                dresses, as seen here with Dr. Wilson.</p>
              <p>Parishioners Mike Moore and Roger Conant are directors for the fund in the United States.
              </p>
              <div class="clearfix"></div>

              <h2 class="mt-3">Supporters of 'ERD'</h2>
              <%= link_to image_tag("https://www.episcopalrelief.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/logo.png",
                alt:"Episcopal Relief &amp; Development", width: '404' , crop: "scale" , class: "d-block mx-auto"
                ), "https://episcopalrelief.org/" %>
                <p class="mt-3">Episcopal Relief and Development is a charity you can trust to use your
                  resources wisely and lovingly. Click the logo above to learn more and make a donation.</p>
                <div class="clearfix"></div>

                <%#= image_tag("https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/saintpaulsnaplesorg/GodLovesNoException.png",
                  width:"95%", class: "d-block mx-auto mt-5" , fetch_format: "auto" ) %>

  </div>
